name: Starbucks
directions: In the back, past the counter. Use the side door if you're not ordering anything, you don't need a special token.

name: Kohl's
directions: Second floor in the back with the shoes and customer service. There's a large, single stall "family bathroom" which is unisex.

name: University Center - University of Houston
directions: Bottom floor of the new UC, behind the Starbucks, labeled "Family Restroom".
comment: The "family restroom" on the main floor is actually just a nursing room. You want the one downstairs.

name: Duncan College - Rice University
directions: Ground floor, by the "A" stairwell.
comment: Nearby campus entrances close at 12 midnight. You might get strange looks if you do not appear to be a student.

name: Mr. Quick's
directions: Near the entrance, there is a hall next to the area where customers order their food.
comment: These bathrooms are... themed? Very girly/masculine. It might make non-binary people uncomfortable (I know it makes me uncomfortable, as I am neutrois). The restrooms are single-stalled.

name: Target
directions: Upstairs near cash registers, accessible also by elevator

name: cosis
directions: nain floor in back of store
comment: can buy an iced tea or coffee

name: McDonalds
directions: Right off the dining room.
comment: I am a transgender woman that works there and have had bo problems using the correct restroom. Mcdonalds policy states that employees and customers alike may use any restroom they identify to.

name: Revolution Kitchen
directions: Behind the wall with pictures hanging on them.
comment: Might have to be a dinner customer

name: 77 Chinese & Hawaii BBQ
directions: In the back but it's a small place, visible from the street
comment: Customers only

name: 2801 Coho St
directions: First and Second floors - located in the center of the building on the 1st floor and right by the stairs and vending machines on 2nd. Dont know about 3rd.

name: Casey's Coffee
directions: In back of shop, grade level
comment: Very clean. At edge of University of Maryland campus, 1 block from bus stop.

name: Publix
street: NW 16th Blvd, Millhopper Shopping Center, Across from Fresh Market
directions: This is a "family" bathroom near the gendered bathrooms.

name: Vanderbilt University Medical Center East
directions: These two unisex, single, accessible restrooms are on the 2nd floor of Medical Center East, which is the ground floor if you are coming in from the 21st Street entrance. If you head straight back from the information desk by the 21st street dropoff circle, they will be on your right  across from the South Tower elevator bay just before the outpatient pharmacy.
comment: These are really only useful if you are already in the hospital area, as parking is a hassle.

name: Christopher's Restaurant and Bar
directions: Hallway in the middle of the rear of the first floor (in line with the front door), clearly marked with unisex/accessible restroom sign to left of door
comment: Went in after I finished eating on the patio, the greeter hadn't seen me previously (shift change) but immediately directed me to the restroom without a question.

name: Target
directions: Down hall on right, just inside entrance. Store hours 8am-10pm M-Sat, 8am-9pm Sun. Sign says "Family", but no one cares if single people  use it

name: Golden Pantry/Exxon
directions: Down hall to left of service counter
comment: Store hours 9am-5pm M-Sat, 10am-4pm Sun. Condom machine in restroom. Staff don't seem to care if you're paying customer or not

name: Publix
directions: Back right of store, near deli
comment: Store hours 7am-10pm. "Family" restroom w/diaper change table, but no one cares if single people are using it

name: WalMart
directions: In back of store, near electronics dept.
comment: Store hours 8am-11pm. Bathroom is "family" one w/diaper change tale and lowered toilet for kids, but no one cares if single people are using it

name: Coffee Lab
directions:
second floor

segundo andar, bem na frente da escada
comment:
just get in, say hi, and use the restroom :]

só entrar, dar olá para os baristas, e usar o banheiro :]

name: Ann Sather
directions: First floor near kitchen
comment: Paying customer.

name: Heroes Sandwich Bar
directions: Go past the counter to the back of the shop, go down the stairs, toilet is at the bottom.
comment: Toilet is for paying customers, but you may be able to sneak by in the lunch rush.

name: 8bit Gaming Bar
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Trader Joe's
directions: Walk straight from the entrance, should be between the vegetable/meat aisles
comment: The bathrooms used to be gendered (as you'll see from the insides, the used to be women's is pink on the inside/used to be men's is just beige) but they changed them both to unisex now.

name: Starbucks
directions: 5th and E street
comment: I think you need to buy something, but they might let you in even if not.  You need to ask the barista for the key code.

name: Seidman College of Buisness
directions: First floor, the hallway to the right, and at the end of the hallway to a slight left
comment: in a public university building

name: Costa (opposite M&S)
directions: Past the till and to the right - well signposted inside.
comment: Paying customer use

name: Downtown Pizza Co.
comment: You should probably tell one of the workers that you're just going in to use the restroom so they know you're not stealing food. They WILL keep an eye on you, especially if it's during a rush time, but you should be able to use the restroom without being bothered.

name: Minnesota Zoo
directions: Family restroom. Enter tropics and Minnesota trails on upper level (whale mural is right outside).
comment: Must be in the zoo to use

name: Bean Around The World
directions: Follow the washroom signs
comment: If you feel awkward about using it, you can go in from the back as they have a little decking area out there. But the people are lovely and if you get asked, just say you're in a difficult situation and you just have to use the washroom. Everyone in there is really LGBTQ friendly and will understand.

name: Julian's
directions: Back of the restaurant, past the kitchen
comment: Reserved for restaurant customers

name: Betty's pies
comment: Need to be a customer- just get a slice of pie :)

name: Target
directions: Unisex family restroom by the Pharmacy

name: Willowbrook Mall
directions: Two single-stall "family" restrooms by the mall's only restroom section

name: Stúdentakjallarinn (at Háskólatorg/University Square)
directions: Stalls in entrance hallway
comment: Open: Sat-Wed 11-23 & Thur-Fri 11-01, 8+ gender neutral single stalls (female & male decals on doors, female decal is a bright color in every case but this does not designate stall gender)

name: Hungry Jacks
comment: You have to be a paying customer, just pretend you're browsing. Its usually too busy to notice. Or just get a cup of water

name: Kopi Cafe
directions: Go to the back, towards the clothing and hippie trinkets in the back. It'll be on your left almost in the very back. 2 stalls, both gender neutral and spacious enough to change.
comment: It's a coffee shop. You should probably buy something, but if you ask nicely and it's not too busy, they seem nice enough that they might let you go.

name: Tom's logging camp
directions: Across from tom's logging camp in tom's too
comment: Open 9-5 Two gender neutral single rooms, one is accessible

name: Caribou Coffee
comment: They signed a pledge to keep their restrooms a safe place for everyone, including trans-people. A purchase is also not necessary.

name: Fat Straw
directions: The bathroom is single occupancy. It's past the counter and to the left.
comment: The bathroom is for customers only and a key is required.

name: Transylvania University
directions: Track level, near elevator
comment: Must have a crimson card on weekends; single stall

name: Walmart
directions: Straight back from the "Home & Pharmacy" doors, there is a single door/stall family restroom.   It will be in front of the "associate only" double doors, on your left hand side.

name: Tap And Barrel
directions: There's a unisex accessible bathroom on the first floor, but it's in the back of the restaurant and may be difficult to get to.

name: Target at Grossmont Center
directions: Upstairs next to the (multi-stall) gendered restrooms. There are also single stall gendered restrooms downstairs near electronics.
comment: If you can't find it, ask an employee. Target is one of the safest places for trans people and I'll always use the restroom there before anywhere else.

name: Walmart
directions: In the back of the store, behind the electronics department, there is a "family bathroom" with a locking door.
comment: It's a crowded part of a busy store. Use caution.

name: Mark's Work Warehouse
directions: Inside the eaton centre, In the back, around a corner. If you ask, they'll tell you to go into the canadian tire (which has gendered restrooms even though they're single stall)
comment: It's best to act like you're browsing first.

name: Parkdale Community Health Centre
directions: southwest corner of queen and dufferin
comment: pair of gender neutral bathrooms on first floor, first door has urinals, both restrooms have baby changing stations

name: University of Idaho
directions: First floor, in front of the Student Account office.
comment: It is a single stall unisex bathroom, wheelchair accessible as well. Open to public as long as the building is open, around every morning at 7am to the evening.

name: Peet's Coffee and Tea
directions: To the right of the coffee grinders
comment: Customers only, key required, high traffic area

name: Ike's Love and Sandwiches
directions: Just past the cashiers
comment: Customers only but chips are like $1.25 (and the staff aren't monsters, they understand nature calling)

name: Vet Medicine Building
directions: Bottom floor, to the right of the first stairway in the middle
comment: For transitioning vet med students or employees specifically

name: Royal Tyrrell Museum
directions: About halfway through the galleries on the ground floor next to the "Triassic Giant" exhibit are two family washroom stalls that are not gendered.
comment: You do have to pay admission to get into the museum~ (these won't be any use unless you already plan to visit the museum - it is a semi-remote location as well)

name: Thompson Regional Community Center
directions: In the play structure room there's a gray single stall that's unisex.
comment: It's free

name: High Street Deli
comment: You should get a sandwich but they're worth the money as any local will tell you.

name: Macy's, The Mall at Whitney Field
directions: Second floor, just outside elevator. Single stall "family" restroom.

name: Valleyfair
directions: On the outside of the sports bar restaurant (formerly Stadium, now Chickie's and Pete's) on the side towards the waterpark.
comment: Must be inside Valleyfair (have purchased a ticket) to use this restroom. Designated as a family restroom but is single-stall and usually unoccupied.

name: Valleyfair
directions: In the restrooms to the left before the turnstiles at the park entrance
comment: Do not have to purchase a ticket to enter the park to use this restroom, but you do have to pay for parking and probably walk a long way through the parking lot. Designated as a family restroom but is usually unoccupied.

name: Lawn Service Center
comment: family bathroom, very clean

name: Sunoco Gas Station
directions: in the far corner of the store, there's a hallway and it's a few doors down
comment: it's not the nicest bathroom in the world, but it's adequate

name: Sierra College Rocklin Campus
directions: Middle of campus near the i buildings or agricultural classrooms.
comment: Large one person bathroom, considered a family bathroom so anyone is allowed.

name: The Smith
directions: Down stairs
comment: Single stalls unmarked, lockable.

name: Fernandez and Wells
directions: Ground floor rear
comment: For paying customers. The only bathrooms in this cafe/restaurant are two large single stalls with no gender signage. It's a tapas & wine bar that doubles up as a coffee & cake shop during the day. New, so gender signage may go up soon but I am hopeful.

name: The Geek Group
directions: In the front lobby
comment: Anybody who wants to pee is welcome to do so. Just say hi if you stop in, anybody/everybody is welcome.

name: Stoney's
directions: around the left side of the bar
comment: you may have to be a paying customer; there are two unisex bathrooms both wheelchair accessible

name: Starbucks
directions: To the left of the service counters.
comment: It is one single unisex stall.

name: Woodlan Jr/Sr High School
directions: Staff bathrooms, between the high school office and the cafeteria.
comment: Ask to use in main office.

name: Hobnob Grille
directions: Two bathrooms on either side of the bar, both are single-stall and just labeled "restroom" with no gendering.

name: Thousand Pound Bend
directions: Looks like a warehouse, actually a really nice alternative scene/cafe
comment: Just walk in and use the toilet, they won't mind :)

name: Stripes Convenience Store and Gas Station
University of Minnesota, Elliott Hall
directions: 5th floor, south portion of building
comment: multi-stall but gender neutral so you are supposed to lock the outer door when you go in (per a sign on door)

name: JJ Bean
comment: Two restrooms, both gender neutral. Need to grab a key from from the front to access the restrooms.

name: Publix
directions: To the right when you enter the store.
comment: Walk right in

name: Governors Square Mall
directions: Near food court

name: Play Louisville
directions: In the lounge area, second right after entering building
comment: May have to pay a cover to enter depending on the night.

name: The Palm
directions: First floor behind the bar.

name: Rochester Institute of Technology, Campus Center, Lower level
directions: Take stairs or elevator to lower level from Welcome Desk at Campus Center entrance; Building is connected to the Student Alumni Union

name: Chimera
directions: both restrooms are single stall & gender neutral.

name: Handmade Burger Co
directions: At the back, to left of the paydesk.
comment: Probably have to be a paying customer, haven't tried otherwise but there are people at the door - however they would probably let you in if you asked, they're nice people!

name: Birthingway College of Midwifery
directions: Main floor of main building has an accessible restroom, all the way back from the front door down the hallway.
comment: All restrooms on campus are single stall. Private college but open to visitors.

name: Transgender Resource Center of New Mexico
directions: You can't miss it once you go inside.
comment: This is the Transgender Resource Center of New Mexico. In addition to a safe, single occupancy, gender neutral restroom, there are also so many services and programs available. Check it out!

name: South Campus Commons 1
directions: Next to the seminar room, across from the Capstone office
comment: Two single room unisex bathrooms. Building only accessible with campus ID outside of business hours.

name: Baked in Kansas City
directions: Back towards the kitchen, take a left.

name: The Crepe House
directions: In the back corner of the restaurant, to the left when entering.
comment: Make a beeline to the restroom if you're not eating there, there's a little hall you can wait in if it is occupied.

name: Pima Community College - Desert Vista Campus
Donnelly's
directions: In the back of the restaurant
comment: 2 single stalls, definitely gendered
